   RICOH CO. (Tokyo) -- Hisashi Kubo, 58 years old, executive
vice president of this maker of copiers, fax machines and
office automation products, returned to the U.S. to serve as
chairman of Ricoh Corp., the U.S. unit. He succeeds Keiji
Endoh, 54, who returned to the parent as managing director in
