<HL>
   First World Cheese Accord
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FWCH
</CO>
<LP>
   MAPLEWOOD, N.J. -- First World Cheese Inc. said it
completed a $12 million, two-year revolving credit agreement
with Bank of Tokyo Trust Co.
   The financing, which is secured by the company's available
assets, replaces the company's prior short-term credit
arrangements with another bank, National State Bank of
Elizabeth, N.J. As of last Thursday, First World's borrowings
under the prior arrangements were about $5.3 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The credit agreement won't include any potential equity
interest for Bank of Tokyo Trust, First World said.
</TEXT>
