<HL>
   Battle Mountain Holding
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BMG WSTW
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Battle Mountain Gold Co. said it will pay $15.8
million and 150,000 common shares to increase its stake in
Empresa Minera Inti Raymi S.A. of Bolivia to 51% from 33.3%.
   The mining concern said it will exercise its option to buy
half the shares, or an 8.8% Inti Raymi stake, from Westworld
Resources Inc. for $7.9 million and 75,000 shares of Battle
Mountain common. It said it will buy the other half, for the
same price, from Zeland Mines S.A., a Panamanian company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   After the transaction is closed, Battle Mountain said it
will have paid a total of $38.8 million and 550,000 common
shares for its share of the Bolivian concern. The transaction
will reduce Westworld's stake in Inti Raymi to 24.5%,
Westworld said.
</TEXT>
