<HL>
   Dividend News:
   Finevest Foods Inc.
   Suspends Dividend
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   FVF
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   GREENWICH, Conn. -- Finevest Foods Inc. said it suspended
its quarterly dividend of three cents a common share because
of a deficit resulting from its 1989 operating loss.
   Finevest, a dairy processor and wholesale distributor of
frozen foods and dairy products in the Southeast, said it
will save about $1.3 million annually from the payout
suspension. The company's 1989 net loss was $19 million on
sales of $700.8 million. The loss included a third-quarter
charge of $10.7 million from restructuring the company's
dairy operations.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   With improved operating efficiencies from the
restructuring and with declining raw-milk costs this spring,
Finevest said it expects its dairy operation to return to
profitability this year.
   Finevest shares fell 50 cents, to close at $7.50, in New
York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday.
</TEXT>
