   Technology:
   General Computer Posts Loss
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GCCC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   TWINSBURG, Ohio -- General Computer Corp., which develops
computer systems for pharmacies and medical offices, posted a
deficit for its fiscal third quarter and said it will receive
$775,000 in interim financing from its chairman, Sidney
Dworkin, to meet capital requirements to fund continuing
operations.
   The company said its loss narrowed to $376,000, or 24
cents a share, for the quarter ended Feb. 28, from $875,000,
or 55 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue fell 15% to $3
million from $3.6 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first nine months, the loss narrowed to $1.8
million, or $1.13 a share, from $2 million, or $1.27 a share,
a year earlier. Revenue rose 3.5% to $8.9 million from $8.6
million.
</TEXT>
