   New Stock Listings
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C18
</SO>
<CO>
   ANE FRG GNV IRL EPT NFC FUND ELMF HOSS SYNL TKOS ULAB VFIC
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The New York Stock Exchange added four new
stock listings, the American Stock Exchange three and the
National Market System of the over-the-counter market seven.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Alliance New Europe Fund Inc. joined the Big Board with
the symbol ANE as an initial public offering. The New York
closed-end investment company invests primarily in equity
securities of European firms.
                                                                                                       

   Emerging Germany Fund Inc. began trading as an initial
public offering with the symbol FRG. The New York closed-end
investment company invests mainly in securities of small and
mid-sized West German companies.
                                                                                                       

   Geneva Steel, a Vineyard, Utah steel products company,
also began trading as an initial public offering, under the
symbol GNV.
                                                                                                       

   Irish Investment Fund Inc. was listed as an initial public
offering with the symbol IRL. The Chicago closed-end
investment company invests primarily in equity securities of
Irish companies. On the American Stock Exchange, Epitope
Inc., a Beaverton, Ore., biotechnology, research and
development company began trading under EPT. The company
previously traded on the over-the-counter market.
                                                                                                       

   Santa Monica Bank, Santa Monica, Calif., will begin
trading capital shares Wednesday under the symbol SMO and
voting trust certificates under the symbol SMV. The company
previously traded over the counter and operates banks in the
metropolitan Los Angeles area.
                                                                                                       

   NFC PLC a Bedford, England, international transport,
logistics, property and services company will begin trading
ADR's Friday under the symbol NFC. The company, whose U.S.
interests include Allied Van Lines Inc., also trades on the
London International Stock Exchange. On the over-the-counter
market, America's All Season Fund Inc., a Winter Park, Fla.,
closed-end investment company will begin trading tomorrow
under the symbol FUND.
                                                                                                       

   Elm Financial Services Inc., an Elmhurst, Ill., bank
holding company for Elmhurst Federal Savings Bank, began
trading under the symbol ELMF.
                                                                                                       

   Hornbeck Offshore Services Inc., a Galveston, Texas,
operator of offshore oil and gas vessels, will start trading
tomorrow under the symbol HOSS.
                                                                                                       

   Syntellect Inc. started trading under the symbol SYNL. The
Phoenix, Ariz., company makes interactive voice response
systems that allow individuals to access computer information
through a touch-tone phone.
                                                                                                       

   Tokos Medical Corp., began trading under the symbol TKOS.
The Santa Ana, Calif., company provides specialized home
health care for pregnant women.
                                                                                                       

   Unilab Corp., a New York medical services and products
holding company that provides laboratory testing services,
will begin trading tomorrow under the symbol ULAB.
                                                                                                       

   VeriFone Inc. will start trading under VFIC. The Redwood
City, Calif., company makes point-of-sale terminals that
automate credit-card payment transactions.
