<HL>
   Business Brief -- J.P. Industries Inc.:
   T&amp;N PLC of Britain Begins
   $190 Million Tender Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.TN JPI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   T&amp;N PLC of Britain said it began its $190 million, or
$17.30-a-share, tender offer for J.P. Industries Inc. The
offer also includes the assumption of $185 million of J.P.
Industries's debt.
   The offer expires midnight April 26 unless extended; it is
conditioned on T&amp;N's ability to attract at least a majority
of J.P. Industries's stock.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   T&amp;N, based in Manchester, England, said it plans to merge
its U.S. auto parts operations into J.P. Industries and make
the Ann Arbor, Mich.-based car, truck and locomotive
engine-parts manufacturer a T&amp;N subsidiary.
   Under terms of the definitive merger agreement reached
last week, T&amp;N will receive $12 million if J.P. Industries is
acquired by another party.
