   International Brief -- Pearson PLC:
   British Publishing Concern's
   '89 Pretax Profit Rose 26%
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.PSO
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Pearson PLC, a British publishing conglomerate that owns
the Financial Times, reported 1989 pretax profit rose 26% to
#250.5 million ($409.7 million) from #198.9 million a year
earlier, helped by gains in all divisions except
entertainment.
   Profit after taxes and minority interests increased 35% to
#171.8 million from #126.9 million. Per-share earnings gained
20% to 67 pence from 55.7 pence. Sales jumped 22% to #1.45
billion from #1.19 billion.
</LP>
