<HL>
   Business Brief -- Philips Industries Inc.:
   Pretax Charge for the Year
   To Total Up to $50 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   PHL MER
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Philips Industries Inc. said it will take a pretax charge
of $45 million to $50 million for the year ended Saturday.
   The Dayton, Ohio, maker of motorhome and housing parts
said it will take an additional pretax charge of as much as
$12 million if a merger agreement with a group formed by
Merrill Lynch Capital Partners Inc., a unit of Merrill Lynch
&amp; Co., is terminated.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The group has been unable to obtain financing for the
proposed offer of $700 million, or $24 a share.
   Philips also said it is providing certain information to
another party that has indicated possible interest in a
transaction with Philips. The company said neither Merrill
Lynch nor any other party has made any new proposals to
Philips.
   The company also said it will sell the following
subsidiaries: Shelby Advanced Automotive Technology Inc.,
Mid-West Conveyor Co., Dearborn Fabricating &amp; Engineering Co.
Shelby makes aluminum wheels for autos, while the other two
make heavy conveyors for the auto industry.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
